Quick Start:
1) Install SAOImage DS9 https://sites.google.com/cfa.harvard.edu/saoimageds9
2) Make scripts donut_gui.py and ds9_start.sh executable 
3) Launch donut_gui.py
4) Push "Select fits" and select it

5)
- In the ds9 window select a single star using "circle region"
- Click "From ds9" button
     or
- fill xc,yc entries
- click "From xc,yc"

6) Click "Fit"

Important
a) copy (or link) donut_KGO.par to donut.par for kgo*.fits and donut_orig.par to donut.par
for focus_orig.fits processing. Do this before running donut_gui.py
b) Toggle INTRA/EXTRA button to select intra/extra-focus images



